<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>美国之音学习英语</title><description>VOA学习英语全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> http://voanews.com <item><title><![CDATA[Right Whale Number Decrease Slowing, But Threats Remain]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/right-whale-number-decrease-slowing-but-threats-remain/7322854.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 10 月 27 日星期五 21:55:22 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/74e35c76- 344c-467e-935b-85c58896f2e5_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;文件 - 北大西洋露脊鲸在科德角海湾近海的表面进食马萨诸塞州普利茅斯，2018 年 3 月 28 日。（美联社照片/Michael Dwyer，档案）&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;北大西洋露脊鲸是世界上最濒危的鲸鱼之一大型鲸鱼&lt;strong>;物种&lt;/strong>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;其种群数量流失速度似乎正在放缓。但科学家警告说，大型海洋动物仍然面临着被捕鱼设备捕获、被船只撞击以及海洋变暖等威胁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.fisheries.noaa. gov/species/north-atlantic-right-whale/overview&quot;>;美国国家海洋和大气管理局 (NOAA) 表示，到 1890 年代初，商业捕鲸船几乎消灭了该物种。它们之所以得名，是因为它们是“正确”的捕鲸鲸鱼，因为它们被杀死时会漂浮在水面上。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;商业鲸鱼捕捞不再是威胁，但其数量从未完全恢复。它们多年来一直受到美国法律的保护。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;北大西洋露脊鲸长约 16 米，重量超过 63,000 公斤。鲸鱼的寿命可能为 70 年。然而，雌性北大西洋露脊鲸现在只能活到 45 岁左右。 &lt;strong>;寿命缩短&lt;/strong>;是人类活动造成的，而不是年老造成的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;NOAA 估计，美国东海岸附近只剩下不到 350 头露脊鲸。从 2010 年到 2020 年，它们的数量减少了约 25%。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;本周，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.narwc.org/&quot;>;北大西洋露脊鲸联盟&lt;/a>; (NARWC) 表示，人口减少似乎已经趋于平稳。 NARWC 表示，2021 年是生育旺盛的一年，共诞生了 18 头小鲸鱼或幼鲸，使鲸鱼数量保持上升。&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl? url=gdb.voanews.com/e3349e08-7340-4855-89df-959156dded56_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;文件 - 2023 年 3 月 27 日，一头北大西洋露脊鲸在马萨诸塞州科德角湾浮出水面。（美联社照片/罗伯特F. Bukaty，文件，NOAA 许可证 # 21371)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;文件 - 2023 年 3 月 27 日，一头北大西洋露脊鲸在马萨诸塞州科德角湾浮出水面。（美联社照片/Robert F . Bukaty，文件，NOAA 许可证 # 21371）&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;但是，该组织警告说，鲸鱼因被捕鱼设备捕获或被船只撞击而导致的大量死亡仍然是一个主要问题鲸鱼。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这个消息没有以前那么糟糕了。我的心情减轻了一些，但肯定不轻松或充满希望，”菲利普·汉密尔顿说。他是 NARWC 的成员，也是新英格兰水族馆安德森卡伯特海洋生物中心的高级科学家。 “不应该依靠鲸鱼产下足够多的幼鲸来&lt;strong>;扭转&lt;/strong>;我们对它们所做的事情。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;科学家表示鲸鱼数量减少的另一个原因海洋变暖和气候变化。鲸鱼吃非常小的海洋生物，称为桡足类动物。它们每年都会从佛罗里达州和佐治亚州海岸附近的产卵场前往新英格兰和加拿大附近的觅食地。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;随着海水变暖，鲸鱼必须离开海洋保护区寻找食物。这使他们很容易受到大型船只的袭击并被困在商业捕鱼设备中。这些是过早死亡的最大原因。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;许多渔民反对拟议的捕捞限制，他们担心这会损害他们的生意，而不是帮助鲸鱼。缅因州龙虾协会前任主席戴夫·库森斯 (Dave Cousens) 称拟议规则“&lt;strong>;毫无意义&lt;/strong>;”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但环保组织希望制定新的联邦规则来拯救该物种，其中包括一项让船只减速以捕鲸。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;我是格雷戈里·斯塔切尔。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;加兰斯·伯克和马特·奥布莱恩为美联社报道了这个故事按。格雷戈里·斯塔切尔为美国之音英语学习频道改编了这个故事。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;___________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;物种&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n 。 &lt;/em>;一组相似的动物或植物，可以产生幼小的动物或植物&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;商业&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;- adj.&lt;/em>;与以下内容相关或用于商品和服务的买卖&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;生命周期&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n。 &lt;/em>;人或动物实际生存的时间&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;反转&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;- v.&lt;/em>;将（某物）改变为相反的状态或条件&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;无意义&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;——形容词。 &lt;/em>;非常愚蠢或愚蠢&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 28 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[New Beatles Song Created with a Little Help from AI]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/new-beatles-song-created-with-a-little-help-from-ai/7328558.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 10 月 27 日星期五 21:58:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- 0aff-0242-ab9e-08dbd66f9b40_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;文件 - 在这张 1966 年 8 月 23 日的档案照片中，披头士乐队（左起），林戈·斯塔尔；保罗·麦卡特尼；约翰列侬;和乔治·哈里森出现在纽约的新闻发布会上。 （美联社照片）&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;甲壳虫乐队的一首“新”歌曲在人工智能的帮助下将于下周推出。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这首歌名为&lt;em>;Now And Then&lt;/em>; 将于 11 月 2 日发行。它与 &lt;em>;Love Me Do&lt;/em>; 是单曲的一部分。 1962 年，&lt;em>;Love Me Do&lt;/em>; 作为披头士乐队的第一首单曲问世。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Now And then &lt;/em>;来自披头士约翰创作的同一组未发行唱片列侬，于 1980 年去世。他的前乐队成员利用一些媒体创作了 20 世纪 90 年代中期发行的歌曲《Free As a Bird》和《Real Love》。&lt;/em>; p>; &lt;p>;保罗·麦卡特尼、林戈·斯塔尔和乔治·哈里森同时制作了&lt;em>;现在&lt;/em>;。但是，技术限制阻碍了他们的进步。乔治·哈里森于 2001 年去世。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在人工智能 (AI) 的帮助下，电影导演彼得·杰克逊能够解决这些技术问题。他使用人工智能将列侬的声音与 20 世纪 70 年代末录音中使用的钢琴声音“分开”​​。更清晰的声音使得幸存的成员麦卡特尼和斯塔尔在去年完成了这首歌。&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/ 6650c2ad-d5e9-4702-9c6e-9734030050e9_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;FILE - 甲壳虫乐队，前景从左至右，保罗·麦卡特尼、乔治·哈里森、约翰·列侬和林戈·斯塔尔在纽约哥伦比亚广播公司“埃德·沙利文秀”上打鼓表演1964 年 2 月 9 日。披头士乐队的“新”歌曲“Now And Then”将于 11 月 2 日星期四推出。（美联社照片/文件）&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;文件 - 披头士乐队，前景从左至右，保罗·麦卡特尼、乔治·哈里森、约翰·列侬和林戈·斯塔尔打鼓，于 1964 年 2 月 9 日在纽约 CBS 的“埃德·沙利文秀”上表演。披头士乐队的一首“新”歌曲。将于 11 月 2 日星期四上市。（美联社照片/文件）&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;新单曲包含哈里森近 30 年前录制的吉他作品。鼓手斯塔尔与麦卡特尼的贝斯、钢琴和吉他一起提供了新的声音。麦卡特尼和斯塔尔还与列侬一起演唱。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;麦卡特尼还添加了在已故披头士乐队制作人乔治·马丁的儿子吉尔斯·马丁的帮助下编写的弦乐器作品。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;而且，他们还编织了背景歌曲来自甲壳虫乐队的第一张唱片《这里、那里和无处不在》、《埃莉诺·里格比》和《因为》。&lt;/em>; p>; &lt;p>;“就是这样，约翰的声音&lt;strong>;水晶&lt;/strong>;清晰，”麦卡特尼在新歌的公告中说道。 “这真是太感人了。我们都在演奏它，”他补充道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;哈里森的&lt;strong>;遗孀&lt;/strong>;奥利维亚说，“如果他还在的话，他会全心全意地”加入保罗和林戈来完成这首歌。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;下周三，即歌曲发行的前一天，一部讲述新唱片故事的 12 分钟影片将被公开。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;本月晚些时候，扩展披头士乐队专辑 &lt;em>;1962-1966&lt;/em>; 和 &lt;em>;1967-1970&lt;/em>; 的版本将发行。后来几年的专辑将添加歌曲&lt;em>;Now And then&lt;/em>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;幸存的披头士乐队巧妙地发布了新项目。他们对旧专辑进行了混音。他们还与杰克逊导演的 2021 年纪录片系列《披头士乐队：归来》合作。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;今年是大结局&lt;strong>;结局&lt;/strong>;披头士乐队的新音乐。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这是有史以来最后一首由四位披头士乐队成员组成的歌曲。约翰、保罗、乔治和林戈，”斯塔尔最近在接受美联社采访时说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;我是凯蒂·韦弗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/ p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;美联社的戴维·鲍德 (David Bauder) 撰写了这份报告。 Caty Weaver 将其改编为美国之音英语学习频道。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;_______________________________________________________&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;水晶&lt;/强>;&lt;em>;- n. &lt;/em>;透明无色的类似水晶的东西&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;寡妇&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n。 &lt;/em>;&lt;em>; &lt;/em>;因死亡而失去配偶或伴侣且通常没有再婚的女性&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;结局&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n. &lt;/em>;某事的结束或终止：例如&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 28 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[“The Legend of Sleepy Hollow,“ by Washington Irving]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/the-legend-of-sleepy-hollow-washington-irving/3579369.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 10 月 27 日星期五 21:59:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/246b526d- c020-4cfb-a625-256ce98bf10b_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:100%&quot; 控件>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small>;&lt;/div >;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/246b526d-c020-4cfb-a625-256ce98bf10b_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;T&quot; style=&quot;width:100%&quot; 控件>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;T&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews. com/246b526d-c020-4cfb-a625-256ce98bf10b_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:100%&quot; 控件>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small >;&lt;/div>;&lt;video poster=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/246b526d-c020-4cfb-a625-256ce98bf10b_tv_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; src=&quot;2&quot; style=&quot;width: 100%”控制>;&lt;/video>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;2&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;audio src=&quot;https://av.voanews.com/clips/ VLE/2014/09/24/bd1e75fa-0f81-4b01-957e-8784f081cde1.mp3&quot;controls>;&lt;/audio>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;断头谷传奇&lt;/small>; &lt;/div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;今天的故事叫《断头谷传奇》。这是关于很久以前在一个名为“断头谷”的山谷中发生的奇怪事情的故事。它的作者是华盛顿·欧文。这个故事由道格·约翰逊讲述。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;被称为断头谷 (Sleepy Hollow) 的山谷隐藏在纽约州的高山上。关于这个安静的山谷有很多故事。但人们最相信的故事却是一个男人在夜间骑马的故事。故事说这个人多年前在美国独立战争期间去世。他的头被击落。每天晚上，他都会从墓地里站起来，跳上马匹，穿过山谷寻找丢失的头颅。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;断头谷附近有一个名叫塔里镇的村庄。许多年前，荷兰人就定居于此。村里有一所小学校。还有一位老师，名叫伊卡博德·克兰 (Ichabod Crane)。伊卡博德·克兰（Ichabod Crane）对他来说是一个好名字，因为他看起来像一只高大的鸟，一只&lt;strong>;鹤&lt;/strong>;。他又高又瘦，像鹤一样。他的肩膀很小，连接着两条修长的手臂。他的头也很小，头顶平。他有一双大耳朵、一双玻璃般的绿色大眼睛和一个长鼻子。&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/AF3660C7-FBDC-4A7A- 8832-50A277925309_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;《断头谷传奇》中的伊卡博德鹤插图&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;《断头谷传奇》中的伊卡博德鹤插图&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p >;&lt;br />; 伊卡博德当老师并没有赚多少钱。而且他虽然又高又瘦，但是吃起来却像个胖子。为了支付食物费用，他教年轻人唱歌赚取额外的钱。每个周日教堂结束后，伊卡博德都会教唱歌。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊卡博德教的女士中有一位是卡特里娜·范·塔塞尔 (Katrina Van Tassel)。她是一位富有的荷兰农民的独生女。她是一个盛开的女孩……很像一个圆圆的红玫瑰色的苹果。伊卡博德对女士们有着一颗柔软而愚蠢的心，很快他就发现自己对范·塔塞尔小姐产生了兴趣。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当伊卡博德看到卡特里娜农场的财富时，他的眼睛睁得大大的：绵延数英里的苹果树和麦田，以及数百只肥胖的农场动物。他把自己视为范塔塞尔农场的主人，卡特里娜是他的妻子。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但有很多问题挡住了卡特里娜的心。其中一位是一位名叫布罗姆·范·布伦特（Brom Van Brunt）的强壮年轻人。布罗姆是所有年轻女士的英雄。他的肩膀很大。他的背很宽。他的头发又短又卷。他总是在塔里镇的赛马比赛中获胜并赢得了许多奖项。布罗姆从来没有没有过一匹马。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;有时在深夜，布罗姆和他的朋友们会骑在马背上大声喊叫，冲过城镇。疲惫的老太太们会从睡梦中醒来，说道：“哎呀，布罗姆·范·布伦特又带着他的狂野队伍来了！”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这就是伊卡博德为了赢得卡特里娜的心而必须击败的敌人。&lt;/p>; &lt;更坚强、更聪明的人不会尝试。但伊卡博德有一个计划。他无法在公开场合与敌人作战。所以他默默地、秘密地做着这件事。他多次拜访卡特里娜的农场，让她认为他正在帮助她唱得更好。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;时间过去了，镇上的人们认为伊卡博德赢了。周日晚上，卡特里娜家里再也没有看到布罗姆的马了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;秋天的一天，伊卡博德被邀请去范塔塞尔家里参加一个大型聚会。他穿着他最好的衣服。一位农民借给他一匹老马，供他长途旅行参加聚会。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;房子里挤满了农民和他们的妻子，红脸的女儿和干净、洗过的儿子。桌子上摆满了不同的吃的东西。酒装满了很多杯。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;布罗姆·范·布伦特 (Brom Van Brunt) 骑着他最快的马“夜魔侠”(Daredevil) 参加聚会。众小姐见到他，都开心地笑了。很快音乐就充满了房间，每个人都开始跳舞唱歌。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊卡博德很高兴与卡特里娜跳舞，布罗姆则用嫉妒的心看着他们。一夜过去了。音乐停止了，年轻人围坐在一起，讲述革命战争的故事。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;很快，断头谷的故事就讲完了。最可怕的故事是关于骑手寻找丢失的头的故事。一位农民讲述了他如何骑着马与无头人赛跑。农夫把他的马跑得越来越快。骑兵跟着穿过灌木丛和石头，直到到达山谷的尽头。无头骑士突然停了下来。他的衣服和皮肤都不见了。只剩下一个白骨在月光下闪闪发亮的男人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;故事结束了，也到了离开聚会的时候了。伊卡博德看上去很高兴，直到他向卡特里娜飓风道晚安。她要结束他们的恋情吗？他离开时感到非常悲伤。卡特里娜见到伊卡博德只是为了让布罗姆·范·布伦特嫉妒，以便他娶她吗？&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;好吧，伊卡博德开始了他在塔里镇周围的山上回家的长途旅程。他一生中从未感到如此孤独。当他靠近多年前一名男子被叛乱分子杀害的那棵树时，他开始吹口哨。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他认为他看到树上有一些白色的东西在移动。但不，只有月光在树上照耀、移动。然后他听到一声响动。他的身体颤抖着。他更快地踢马。老马想跑，却差点掉进河里。伊卡博德再次击中马匹。马跑得很快，然后突然停了下来，差点把伊卡博德摔倒在地。&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/00F9F522-3096 -4EDC-8D69-B002B73906DA_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;断头谷追逐&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;断头谷追逐&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;那里，在河边的黑暗树林里，灌木丛低矮，矗立着一个丑陋的东西。又大又黑。它一动不动，但似乎像一个巨大的怪物一样准备跳跃。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊卡博德的头发直立起来。已经来不及逃跑了，在恐惧中，他做了他唯一能做的事。他颤抖的声音打破了寂静的山谷。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你是谁？”那东西没有回答。伊卡博德再次问道。仍然没有答案。伊卡博德的老马开始前行。黑色的东西开始在黑暗中沿着伊卡博德的马侧移动。伊卡博德让他的马跑得更快。那黑色的东西随着他们一起移动。他们并排移动，一开始很慢。但一言不发。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊卡博德的心沉了下去。他们上了一座小山，在树影上方移动。有一瞬间，月亮落了下来，令伊卡博德惊恐的是，他发现那是一匹马。它有一个骑手。但骑手的头不在他的身上。它在骑手的前面，停在马上。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;伊卡博德用尽全力踢打他的老马。他们冲过灌木丛和树林，穿过断头谷山谷。前面是一座古老的教堂桥，无头骑士在那里停下来，返回他的埋葬地。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“如果我能先到达那里，我就安全了，”伊卡博德想。他又踢了马一脚。马跃上桥，疾驰而过，声音如雷。伊卡博德回头看看无头人是否已经停下来。只见那人抬起他的头，用强大的力道扔了出去。头部击中了伊卡博德的脸部，并将他从马背上撞到了下面的泥土中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;第二天，他们发现伊卡博德的马正在安静地吃草。他们找不到伊卡博德。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们走过了整个山谷。他们看到了伊卡博德的马在山谷中奔跑时留下的脚印。他们甚至在桥附近的灰尘中发现了伊卡博德的旧帽子。但他们没有找到伊卡博德。他们唯一发现的其他东西就在伊卡博德的帽子附近。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;那是一个圆形橙色南瓜的碎片。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;镇上的人们谈论伊卡博德已经好几个星期了。他们还记得山谷里那些可怕的故事。最后，他们相信无头骑士已经把伊卡博德带走了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;很久以后，一位老农民从纽约市回来。他说他确信他在那里看到了伊卡博德。他认为伊卡博德默默离开断头谷是因为他失去了卡特里娜。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;至于卡特里娜，当她嫁给布罗姆·范·布伦特时，她的父母为她举办了一场盛大的婚礼。许多参加婚礼的人都看到，每当提到伊卡博德的名字时，布罗姆都会微笑。他们想知道为什么当有人谈论在伊卡博德满是灰尘的旧帽子附近发现的破碎的橙色南瓜时，他为什么大声笑。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;现在轮到你了。你们国家最著名的鬼故事有哪些？请在评论部分或在我们的 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/voalearningenglish/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;Facebook 页面&lt;/a>;上给我们写信。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt; p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;__________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;测验&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;你对这个故事的理解程度如何？&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;_________________________________&lt;br />; &lt;/h2>; &lt; h2>;对于教师&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;这个教师课程计划包含教授故事预测策略的活动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;__________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt; /h2>; &lt;h2>;&lt;strong>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/strong>;&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;埋葬&lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n.&lt;/em>;将死者埋葬在坟墓中的行为或仪式&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;起重机&lt;/strong>; - &lt;em>;n.&lt;/em>;一种高大的鸟，有长脖子和长腿，住在水边&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;反叛者&lt;/strong>;–&lt;strong>; &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;n.&lt;/em>;反对或反对政府的人&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;&lt;em>;&lt;em>;&lt;em>;&lt;em>;&lt;strong>;革命战争&lt;/strong>; – n. &lt;/em>;&lt;/em>;&lt;/em>;&lt;/em>;美国脱离英国独立的战争&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;动摇&lt;/strong>; –&lt;em>; v&lt;/em>;。你的声音：因为你紧张、生气、悲伤等而以不稳定的方式发出声音&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 28 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[This and That]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/this-and-that/7328363.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 10 月 27 日星期五 22:05:49 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- 0a00-0242-5d19-08dbd649089c_r1_s.png&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>; &lt;div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;您好！本周&lt;em>;向老师提问&lt;/em>;，我们回答了一个关于使用“this、that、these、 those”的问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;问题&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;你好，&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;请问我应该如何使用代词“这个，那个，这些，那些” ”超越了近或远的&lt;strong>;概念&lt;/strong>;？&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;非常感谢，&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;Odilon&lt; /p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;回答&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;感谢您的来信，奥迪隆。这是一个很好的问题！&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;我们知道“this、that、these、 those”这些词在英语中有很多含义和用途。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;“这个/这些”的一个含义是指出某人或某物在物理距离上很近。 “那个/那些”可以表示物理距离较远的某人或某物。以下是两个示例：&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;您可以一边拿着一边说“&lt;u>;这本书&lt;/u>;是我的”它在你手里。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;你可以一边指着一边说“&lt;u>;那本书&lt;/u>;是你的”房间对面的桌子上有一张。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;时间&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;近和远也可以显示时间。 “This”可以表示现在或当前，“that”可以表示之前或之前。例如，&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;太阳能&lt;strong>;月食&lt;/strong>;今年&lt;u>;&lt;/u>;不会再发生。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt; em>;最后一次超级月亮出现在九月。&lt;u>;那时&lt;/u>;，月球的轨道比平常更接近地球。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;In第一句中的“this”表示当前年份。第二句中的“that”表示过去的某个时间。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;偏好&lt;/strong>; &lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;我们还可以使用“this/that”来表示偏好或理想的选择。“This”可以表示更理想的选择，“that”可以表示不太理想的选择以下是两个示例：&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;&lt;u>;这是我最喜欢的餐厅。&lt;/em>; &lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;&lt;u>;这&lt;/u>;听起来不太有趣。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt; /div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;第一句中的“this”表明该餐厅是最佳选择，第二句中的“that”表明该想法不是理想的选择。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;焦点或注意力&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;“这个/这些”还有一个额外的用途。我们可以使用“这个/这些”作为焦点或注意力，以建立新的信息。使用“这个/这些”可以将读者或听众的注意力引导到重要信息上。这是一个例子。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:40px&quot;>;&lt;em>;&lt;u>;这&lt;/u>;是人工智能使用的一个主要问题：所有权。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;“This”引导读者注意句子中出现的新信息。句子中的重要信息是主要关注点。所有权是主要问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;请告诉我们这个解释是否对您有帮助，Odilon。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;您有吗关于美式英语的问题？请发送电子邮件至 &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:learningenglish@voanews.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;learningenglish@voanews.com&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;那就是&lt;em>;请教老师&lt;/em>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;我是 Gena Bennett。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt; /div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;吉娜·贝内特 (Gena Bennett) 为美国之音英语学习平台撰写了本课程。 &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;_____________________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的文字&lt;/h2>; &lt;/div >; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;概念&lt;/strong>;–&lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;。想法或信仰&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;日食&lt;/strong>;–&lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;。太阳被月亮遮挡或月亮穿过地球阴影的事件&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>; &lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 28 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Researchers Detect Ancient Energetic Burst]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/researchers-detect-ancient-energetic-burst-/7322964.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 10 月 26 日星期四 21:55:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/83ec49f4- 4a01-4776-b8b8-ae0be83e4262_cx0_cy4_cw0_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;此艺术家的印象（未按比例）说明了来自在这张 2023 年 10 月 20 日获得的讲义图片中，它起源于遥远的星系，一路到达地球。（ESO/M. Kornmesser/来自 REUTERS 的讲义）&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>; &lt;p>;天文学家&lt;strong >; 检测到&lt;/strong>;来自大约 80 亿年前看起来像是星系连接的无线电波。这一发现是已知最古老的难以解释事件的例子：快速无线电&lt;strong>;爆发&lt;/strong>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;不到&lt;strong>;科学家表示，这次爆发释放的能量相当于太阳在 30 年内释放的能量。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;澳大利亚 SKA 探路者号，位于西澳大利亚州的射电望远镜澳大利亚，检测到爆炸。位于智利的欧洲南方天文台甚大望远镜是最强大的望远镜之一，发现了爆发的&lt;strong>;位置&lt;/strong>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;快速射电暴，或FRB，是一种射频电磁辐射。它持续时间不到一毫秒，但胜过宇宙中大多数其他无线电波源。无线电波在电磁波谱中具有最长的波长。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;澳大利亚斯威本科技大学天文学家 Ryan Shannon 是最近发表在《科学》杂志上的这项研究的共同领导者.&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;他说快速射电暴中的无线电波与微波炉中使用的无线电波类似。他补充说，这个快速射电暴拥有微波加热“一碗两倍于太阳大小的爆米花”所需的能量。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;到目前为止，已知最古老的此类快速射电暴爆发时间可追溯至 50 亿年前，这使得这次爆发的年龄比之前大了 30 亿年。宇宙大约有138亿年的历史。相比之下，地球大约有 45 亿年的历史。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;在观察很久以前的物体和事件时，研究人员会跨越很远的距离进行观察，使得这次爆发也是有史以来最远的快速射电暴检测到。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;“我们现在知道，快速射电暴已经存在了宇宙一半以上的年龄，”研究联合领导者、澳大利亚麦考瑞大学的 Stuart Ryder 说道。 .&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;研究人员于 2007 年首次发现快速射电暴。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;最有可能的来源是一种特殊的“&lt;strong >;中子星&lt;/strong>;，称为磁星。这些恒星......是宇宙中最极端的物体，需要它们才能产生如此极端的爆发，”香农说。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;“还有更多的高能事件在宇宙中，与&lt;strong>;恒星&lt;/strong>;爆炸或黑洞&lt;strong>;粉碎&lt;/strong>;恒星有关。但快速射电暴的独特之处在于它们以无线电波的形式产生所有能量，而在其他波段（例如可见光或 X 射线）中看不到任何能量，而且信号非常短，”香农补充道。 &lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;香农解释说，它们也更常见，每天大约有 100,000 起事件发生在宇宙的某个地方。香农说，检测到的数量要少得多，只有大约 50 起 - 包括这个 - 已被&lt;strong>;追溯到&lt;/strong>;到它们开始的星系。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;科学家们表示，研究这些爆发可以帮助探测和测量大的爆发据信，存在于星系之间的大距离空间中的物质数量。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;我是约翰·拉塞尔。&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/ p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;威尔·邓纳姆 (Will Dunham) 为路透社报道了这篇报道。约翰·拉塞尔 (John Russell) 为美国之音英语学习频道改编了该报道。&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p >;________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;这个故事中的单词&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;检测&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;-- v. &lt; /em>; 发现或注意到某物的存在&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;爆发&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n.&lt;/em>; 短暂的生产或做事突然开始的事情&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;毫秒&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n.&lt;/em>;千分之一秒&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;位置&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>; -- n。 &lt;/em>;一个地方或位置&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;中子星&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n.&lt;/em>;一种小型且非常致密的恒星物体&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;恒星&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;——形容词&lt;/em>;属于恒星或与恒星有关&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt; p>;&lt;strong>;切碎&lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– v.&lt;/em>;将（某物）切成长片&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;独特&lt;/强>;&lt;em>;——形容词。 &lt;/em>;用来表示某事或某人与其他任何事物或任何人不同&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>; &lt;div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;trace &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;-- v. &lt;/em>;追随某事的原因或开始&lt;/p>; &lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 27 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[US Program Could Permit Visa Holders to Renew in US]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/us-program-could-permit-visa-holders-to-renew-in-us/7324567.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023 年 10 月 26 日星期四 21:56:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000- c0a8-0242-c0a3-08db896660c8_cx0_cy7_cw0_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;文件 - VFS Global 签证申请中心位于土耳其伊斯坦布尔。 2022 年 2 月 25 日。&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;美国国务院正在制定一项测试计划，允许一些工作签证持有者在美国&lt;strong>;更新&lt;/strong>;他们的文件。&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>; p>; &lt;p>;试点计划将涉及 H-1B 签证持有者。这种签证允许高技能外国人进入美国工作至少三年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;目前，H-1B 签证持有者需要前往美国境外的美国外交机构寻求续签。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国国务院发言人告诉美国之音，该试点计划旨在改善临时雇用 H-1B 员工的“美国公司经常遇到的&lt;strong>;不确定性&lt;/strong>;”。该官员通过电子邮件进行了沟通。官员在不愿透露姓名的情况下接受了美国之音的采访。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该官员表示，国务院将判断政策变化是否会提高全球签证审批的可用性和速度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;移民律师长期以来一直敦促乔·拜登总统的政府恢复2004年终止的美国签证续签。他们表示，目前的续签程序可能会使美国的外国雇员很难获得美国驻外外交机构的任命。与这些任命相关的差旅费用可能非常昂贵。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;发言人表示，国务院希望在今年年底前开始接受续签文件。 The program is to begin with officials inviting a small number of visa holders to take part.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But the spokesperson said the program must first go through a rule-making process, which will start at the White House. Once those rules are decided, the State Department will seek public comments and consider any necessary changes. The proposal will then go back to the White House for final review.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Bryan Lynn.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Aline Barros reported this story for VOA News. Bryan Lynn adapted the report for Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;_________________________________________&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;renew &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– v. &lt;/em>;to arrange to continue an official agreement that is set to end soon&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;uncertainty &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– adj. &lt;/em>;not sure or not able to decide about something&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 27 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[China Sends Its Youngest-ever Crew, Enters New Space Race]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/china-sends-its-youngest-ever-crew-enters-new-space-race/7328287.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Thu, 26 Oct 2023 21:58:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/ef037c24-954d-46e1-afbd-1582a76c8a3c_cx0_cy5_cw0_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;Chinese astronauts for the Shenzhou-17 mission, from left, Jiang Xinlin, Tang Hongbo and Tang Shengjie wave as they attend a send-off ceremony for their manned space mission at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwestern China on October 26, 2023. (AP Photo/Andy Wong)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;China launched its youngest-ever crew for its orbiting space station Thursday. The launch is part of the country&#39;s plan to put astronauts on the moon before 2030.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Shenzhou 17 &lt;strong>;spacecraft&lt;/strong>; lifted off from the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwestern China at 03:14 UTC. The China Manned Space Agency said the average age of the three-member crew is the youngest since the launch of the space station. Their average age is 38, state media China Daily said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The three astronauts are Tang Hongbo, Tang Shengjie, and Jiang Xinlin. They will replace a crew that has been on the station for six months.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The new crew will perform experiments in space medicine, space technology, and other areas during their &lt;strong>;mission&lt;/strong>;. And they will help to place and do possible repairs to equipment inside and outside the station, the agency said.&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/0ce378c7-44b1-479a-8a9b-619efd0671f0_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;A Long March rocket carrying a crew of Chinese astronauts in a Shenzhou-17 spaceship lifts off at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwestern China on October 26, 2023. (AP Photo/Andy Wong)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;A Long March rocket carrying a crew of Chinese astronauts in a Shenzhou-17 spaceship lifts off at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwestern China on October 26, 2023. (AP Photo/Andy Wong)&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;New space race&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China also has plans to place astronauts on the moon before the end of 2030 in competition with the United States in space exploration. This follows other competition for influence between the world&#39;s two largest economies in the technology, military, and diplomatic fields.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Earlier on Wednesday, the Chinese space agency also announced plans to send a new telescope to look deep into the universe. Chinese state broadcaster CCTV said the telescope would permit for mapping of the sky, but no timeline was given for when it would be placed.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In 2022, the Chinese government built its own space station after it was not permitted to join the US-led International Space Station. The Americans worried that the Chinese space program was under the control of its military, the People&#39;s Liberation Army.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China&#39;s first manned space mission in 2003 made it the third country after the former Soviet Union and the US to put a person into space using its own resources.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The American space program is believed to be far ahead of China at this time. But, China has made some important steps. They include bringing back &lt;strong>;samples&lt;/strong>; from the moon&#39;s surface for the first time in many years and landing a vehicle on the less explored far side of the moon.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The US, meanwhile, aims to put astronauts back on the moon&#39;s surface by the end of 2025. It is aided by private American companies like SpaceX and Blue Origin.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In addition to their moon, or lunar, programs, the two countries have also separately landed vehicles on Mars. And China plans to follow the US in landing a spacecraft on an &lt;strong>;asteroid&lt;/strong>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Gregory Stachel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Andy Wong reported this story for The Associated Press. Gregory Stachel adapted the story for VOA Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;_______________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;spacecraft &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. something (such as a leaf, skeleton, or footprint) that is from a plant or animal which lived in ancient times and that you can see in some rocks&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;mission &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. a flight by an aircraft or spacecraft to perform a specific task&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;sample &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– n.&lt;/em>; a small amount of something that gives you information about the thing it was taken from&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;asteroid &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. any one of thousands of small planets that circle around the sun&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 27 Oct 2023 06:07:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Grammar and Halloween]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/grammar-and-halloween-/7326228.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Thu, 26 Oct 2023 22:05:23 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-0a00-0242-4cc8-08dbd581255f_r1_s.png&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;An interesting holiday in the United States is coming up soon. Halloween happens on the last day of October. If you have lived in the US, you have probably noticed many changes in the month or so before Halloween. Let&#39;s hear about some of them and explore the vocabulary and expressions you might hear this time of year.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&#39;Trick-or-treat&#39;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;First, you should know about trick-or-treating. Children &lt;strong>;dress&lt;/strong>; &lt;strong>;up&lt;/strong>; in special clothes, or costumes, to look like frightening creatures. They might dress up as little &lt;strong>;vampires&lt;/strong>;, &lt;strong>;ghosts&lt;/strong>; and &lt;strong>;witches &lt;/strong>;or superheroes. Then their parents walk with them to the homes of neighbors, where the children knock at the door and call out, “Trick or treat!”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Some people believe the custom goes back to an old Celtic celebration in which people went from door to door asking for firewood. The Celts believed that the spirits of the dead would return to their homes on October 31, the day of the autumn feast. The Celts would build large fires to frighten away evil spirits on that night.&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/013b0000-0aff-0242-48c7-08dabc073e50_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;FILE - President Joe Biden and first lady Jill Biden give treats to trick-or-treaters on the South Lawn of the White House, on Halloween, Oct. 31, 2022, in Washington. (AP Photo/Alex Brandon)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;FILE - President Joe Biden and first lady Jill Biden give treats to trick-or-treaters on the South Lawn of the White House, on Halloween, Oct. 31, 2022, in Washington. (AP Photo/Alex Brandon)&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;In modern-day Halloween, the children ask for candy. That&#39;s the “treat” part. The “trick” part is what happens if you do not give them something.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Before Halloween, communities might create a “&lt;strong>;haunted&lt;/strong>; house” in an old house or an open field. Visitors can walk through the place and be frightened and surprised by unusual noises and people dressed up like ghosts or spirits.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fear plays a big part in Halloween celebrations. The words we use to talk about fear include “scary,” an adjective to show something causes fear and “afraid” an adjective that describes the person who feels fear. We might say, “I&#39;m scared of ghosts,” to say we are afraid of ghosts.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Another word we use to describe things that cause fear is “&lt;strong>;spooky&lt;/strong>;.” Little people trying to look like ghosts might say, “Boo!” to frighten others. Let&#39;s put some of these expressions together to see how they work.&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;Greg has a really scary costume this year. He said “Boo!” to me and I jumped!&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;Caty&#39;s house looks really spooky with all those skeletons and spider webs that she put out in her yard.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;I&#39;m not afraid of ghosts but seeing people dressed up as witches scares me!&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;You will see that stores begin offering many kinds of candies in small packages. We call these “individually wrapped” treats. They are meant for handing out to children as part of trick-or-treating. Some candy makers call these small packages “fun-sized” treats.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Halloween decorations&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;People put some strange things on and around their homes for Halloween. People hang toy spiders, skeletons and other scary &lt;strong>;decorations&lt;/strong>; on trees and bushes. You will see pumpkins everywhere. People often empty the pumpkins and make scary faces on them. Then they place a candle inside so the pumpkin face shines in the night. We call these “jack-o-lanterns.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The custom of carving scary faces into vegetables is believed to come to us from the Irish. They had an old story about a wandering soul named Stingy Jack. They carved faces in turnips to frighten him away. When they came to America, they found the pumpkin was widely available. So, they carved faces into pumpkins, and made what we call the jack-o-lantern today. Now, children carry plastic buckets made to look like a carved pumpkin. They fill them with candy as they trick-or-treat around their neighborhood.&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/2E20AB1C-C1F4-47D3-AA34-DC4721EBDAED_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;FILE - Pumpkin Jack O&amp;#39; Lanterns sit on the grounds of the historic Van Cortlandt Manor House and Museum during the &quot;Great Jack O&amp;#39; Lantern Blaze&quot; in Croton-on Hudson, New York, Oct. 27, 2015. (REUTERS/Mike Segar)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;FILE - Pumpkin Jack O&amp;#39; Lanterns sit on the grounds of the historic Van Cortlandt Manor House and Museum during the &quot;Great Jack O&amp;#39; Lantern Blaze&quot; in Croton-on Hudson, New York, Oct. 27, 2015. (REUTERS/Mike Segar)&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;We close with a usual conversation around Halloween in the US See how many traditions and customs you can spot.&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;A: Are you going to any Halloween parties this year?&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;B: No, I have to take my kids trick-or-treating. Then I&#39;m too tired to dress up and go out to a party. Are you going?&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;A: Yes, I&#39;m going to be a vampire this year. My block has a great party with a haunted house every year.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;B: Oh, I wish I could go. Hey, will you help me carve these pumpkins? I want to put them out front.&lt;br />; B: Sure, I love carving jack-o-lanterns. Can I have some of that candy while I&#39;m working?&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:48px&quot;>;&lt;em>;A: Of course. Help yourself to those fun-sized Hershey bars. I only have a hundred of them.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Does your culture have any celebrations where you dress up or give out treats? Write to us in the comments to tell us about them!&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;And that&#39;s Everyday Grammar for Halloween. Boo!&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Jill Robbins.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Jill Robbins wrote this lesson for Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;_________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;dress up &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– v.&lt;/em>; to wear a special kind of clothing for a festival or event&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;vampire – &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;n. &lt;/em>;a dead person who leaves the grave at night to bite and suck the blood of living people&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;ghost – &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;n. &lt;/em>;the soul of a dead person thought of as living in an unseen world or as appearing to living people&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;witch – &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;n. &lt;/em>;a woman who is thought to have magic powers&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;candy – &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;n. &lt;/em>;a sweet food made with sugar or chocolate&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;What do you think of this lesson? Let us know in the forum below.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 27 Oct 2023 06:07:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[US, Australia to Provide Underwater Internet Cables for Pacific Islands]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/us-australia-to-provide-underwater-internet-cables-for-pacific-islands/7326364.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Wed, 25 Oct 2023 21:56:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/800f0000-c0a8-0242-b6bf-08db049139c4_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;FILE - Ships are docked offshore near Honiara, the capital of the Solomon Islands, Nov. 24, 2018. Google will work together with the United States and Australia to offer internet service to Pacific Island nations. (AP Photo/Mark Schiefelbein, File)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;The technology company Google will work together with the United States and Australia to offer internet service to Pacific Island nations such as Tuvalu.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The agreement continues a project Google is working on in the area.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The announcement came on the same day that Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese visited with US President Joe Biden at the White House.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The state visit has been planned for a long time.&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/337a3924-2c73-40eb-9aef-25de5295c9ce_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;US President Joe Biden and Australia&amp;#39;s Prime Minister Anthony Albanese leave a joint press conference at the Rose Garden of the White House in Washington, DC on October 25, 2023. (Photo by SAUL LOEB / AFP)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;US President Joe Biden and Australia&amp;#39;s Prime Minister Anthony Albanese leave a joint press conference at the Rose Garden of the White House in Washington, DC on October 25, 2023. (Photo by SAUL LOEB / AFP)&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;The underwater cable project will bring internet service to Tuvalu, Micronesia, Kiribati, the Marshall Islands, Papua New Guinea, the Solomon Islands, Timor-Leste and Vanuatu.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A Biden administration official said Australia will provide $50 million for the project and the US will give $15 million.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Pacific islands are an area of interest for both the US and China. Each nation has been working to expand their relationships with the island nations. They have been promising military partnerships and building projects.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Biden has said work by US telecommunications and internet companies such as Google is a national security issue. The companies that own or oversee cables that connect small countries to the internet can control the flow of information around the world.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;For example, Google, which is owned by parent company Alphabet, is working on a cable project that links Taiwan with the US and the Philippines.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A United States official told Reuters the Pacific islands will get help with&lt;strong>; cybersecurity&lt;/strong>; as part of the project.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Dan Friedell.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Dan Friedell adapted this story for Learning English based on a report by Reuters.&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;cybersecurity – &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;n. &lt;/em>;work done to protect computer systems and stored information from unauthorized access&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;We want to hear from you. What is the internet service like where you live?&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 26 Oct 2023 06:07:05 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan Prepares to Deport Illegal Afghans]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/pakistan-prepares-to-deport-illegal-afghans/7326204.html]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;Wed, 25 Oct 2023 21:57:00 GMT&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/ddb72e6e-86fe-4073-93a7-b010d5f81de8_cx0_cy4_cw0_r1_s_w900.jpg&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;>;&lt;div>;&lt;small style=&quot;color: #999;&quot;>;FILE - Afghan refugees board a bus from Karachi, Pakistan, to Afghanistan on Sept. 21, 2023. Pakistan, on Oct. 3, 2023, ordered undocumented immigrants to leave the country by Nov. 1. (Photo by Rizwan TABASSUM / AFP)&lt;/small>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;The Pakistani government has approved the creation of several &lt;strong>;deportation&lt;/strong>; centers for hundreds of thousands of Afghans living illegally in the country. Pakistan plans to arrest and send the Afghan nationals back to Afghanistan starting next month.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government recently approved the Illegal Foreigners Repatriation Plan. It sets a November 1 &lt;strong>;deadline&lt;/strong>;. The deadline is for all “illegal/unregistered foreigners” and those overstaying their visas. These groups are required to return to their countries. If they do not, they face deportation for breaking Pakistan&#39;s immigration laws.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Pakistani Interior Minister Sarfaraz spoke when the deadline was announced in early October. He said an estimated 1.7 million Afghans are among those facing deportation.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Official &lt;strong>;sources&lt;/strong>; told VOA that special deportation centers would be established in four areas: Punjab, Sindh, Baluchistan, and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Afghans detained in Punjab and Sindh will be moved to centers in the Rawalpindi and Karachi areas.&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-c0a8-0242-37f5-08dbc71ba741_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;FILE - Afghan families wait to board a bus to depart for their homeland, in Karachi, Pakistan, Oct. 6, 2023. Pakistan&amp;#39;s government announced a major crackdown on illegal migrants in the country. (AP Photo/Fareed Khan)&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;FILE - Afghan families wait to board a bus to depart for their homeland, in Karachi, Pakistan, Oct. 6, 2023. Pakistan&amp;#39;s government announced a major crackdown on illegal migrants in the country. (AP Photo/Fareed Khan)&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;Khyber Pakhtunkhwa will have two deportation centers in Nowshehra and Chamkani. While Baluchistan will have three centers: one in the capital of Quetta, and others in the areas of Pishin and Qilla Abdullah districts. These two areas are on Pakistan&#39;s 2,600-kilometer border with Afghanistan. Most refugee families are in those areas.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The new plan &lt;strong>;empowers&lt;/strong>; local administrations, police, and other officials to detain and deport Afghan nationals illegally living in the country. The plan also says that individuals charged with or on trial for minor crimes will be sent out of the country. It also says that those charged with or facing trial for “serious crimes” will not be sent back to Afghanistan.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Pakistan has promised to carry out the deportations in “a &lt;strong>;phased &lt;/strong>;and orderly” way. It also said that it would not target the 1.4 million Afghan refugees living legally in the country. The government added it would not target 900,000 Afghan citizens who are registered in Pakistan as economic migrants.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government has told law enforcement agencies not to &lt;strong>;harass&lt;/strong>; legal refugees and those with Afghan nationality documents. However, Afghanistan&#39;s Taliban rulers and refugee families have claimed that some Afghans experienced abuse and mistreatment from the police.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Taliban have called on Pakistan to reconsider the deportation plan, calling it “&lt;strong>;inhumane&lt;/strong>;” and “unacceptable.” However, they have recently set up special camps on the Afghan side of the border. The camps will provide immediate shelter, health care, food, and financial assistance to families returning from the neighboring country.&lt;/p>; &lt;div >;&lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl?url=gdb.voanews.com/01000000-0aff-0242-373d-08dbd48a68a8_w900.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;FILE - Afghans returning from Pakistan in this undated photo.&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/>;&lt;span>;FILE - Afghans returning from Pakistan in this undated photo.&lt;/span>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p>;Officials in both countries have confirmed that tens of thousands of Afghans have voluntarily returned to their home country since Pakistan announced the deadline nearly a month ago.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Taliban spokesman Zabihullah Mujahid on Afghan television urged Pakistan to treat Afghan refugees “humanely” and extend the period of deportation. He asked all the refugees to return to their country. He said the Taliban has made Afghanistan into a “safer and better” place.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;Taliban rule in Afghanistan &lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Taliban seized power from a US-backed government in August 2021. At that time, US and NATO troops left the country after nearly 20 years of involvement in the Afghan war.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;After the Taliban took over, hundreds of thousands of people fled to Pakistan. They feared punishment for their connections to Western forces. They included human rights defenders, former government officials, professionals, female activists and reporters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Many have since moved to the US and other Western countries. But thousands are waiting in hopes of immigrating to the United States or Europe.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Taliban has enforced Islamic law in the country. The group has barred &lt;strong>;teenage &lt;/strong>;girls from schools and many women from work. The restrictions mean many refugee families do not want to return to Afghanistan. They say their daughters cannot seek education or work in the country.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The United Nations has urged Pakistan to suspend its deportation plan. It warns the plan could mean Afghans will be subject to abuse by the country&#39;s ruling Taliban officials.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;I&#39;m Gregory Stachel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Ayaz Gul reported this story for Voice of America. Gregory Stachel adapted the story for VOA Learning English. &lt;/em>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;________________________________________________&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>; &lt;/h2>; &lt;h2>;Words in This Story&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;deport &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;. to force (a person who is not a citizen) to leave a country&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;deadline &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;n&lt;/em>;. a date or time when something must be finished&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;source &lt;/strong>;–n. a person who tells a reporter information&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;empower &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;. to give official authority or legal power to (someone)&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;phased &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– adj.&lt;/em>; done gradually in steps and according to a plan&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;harass &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;v&lt;/em>;. to annoy or bother (someone) in a constant or repeated way&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;humane &lt;/strong>;&lt;em>;– adj.&lt;/em>; kind or gentle to people or animals&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;teenage &lt;/strong>;– &lt;em>;adj&lt;/em>;. between 13 and 19 years old&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 26 Oct 2023 06:07:05 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>